<TEXT>
<P>
One of my favorite shows, "The Young Riders," was pulled from its time slot in 
mid-season. 
</P>
<P>
It was given little advertising but found an audience and started to move up 
(in the ratings) when it was replaced by "Twin Peaks." Due to a lot of hype and 
marketing by ABC, this "innovative" "Peaks" series with its "brilliant 
director" had good ratings in the beginning, but interest dwindled. "The 
Riders" survived to a second season. But as the Emmys passed "Peaks" by, I 
wondered: What was all the fuss about? 
</P>
<P>
Anathea Lopez, Baldwin Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
