</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
AT HOME; 
</P>
<P>
SOAPY INSIDER TRADING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN TUCKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOAP OPERA LOVERS are as rabid about their passion as sports fans are about 
theirs. And if actor Jim Warren, creator of Soap Star! trading cards, has his 
way, you may soon be hearing, "I'll trade you a Billy Warlock for a Melissa 
Brennan." 
</P>
<P>
A Soap Star! set ($6) -- which includes 12 full-color cards, one of which is a 
soap alumnus who's made it big -- features such popular performers as Kin 
Shriner (Scott) of "General Hospital" and Robin Mattson (Gina) of "Santa 
Barbara" and provides bios and little-known facts about the stars. 
"Surprisingly," Warren says, "one of every 10 orders is from a man." 
</P>
<P>
