<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED MEDIA: *** "ONE FAIR SUMMER EVENING" NANCI GRIFFITH ; MCA MUSIC VIDEO 
LASER DISC ($24.95); 
</P>
<P>
ITEMS IN THIS PERIODIC SURVEY OF POP-RELATED BOOKS, VIDEOCASSETTES AND LASER 
DISCS ARE RATED ON A SCALE OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBERT HILBURN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What more can you ask of a video than it turn someone who was only mildly 
interested in a veteran performer into a fan? Part of the credit on "Evening" 
goes to director Bud Schaetzle, who has done an excellent job of capturing the 
intimacy of a Griffith club performance in this modest but winning 45-minute 
package. But the video's most important element is Griffith herself. A 
singer-songwriter whose artful, warm music blends elements of country and folk, 
Griffith sometimes seems a bit too understated on record, but she blossoms here 
with a series of songs that are equally rich in detail and spirit. ROBERT 
HILBURN 
</P>
