<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHILD PROOF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Where the little darlings are welcome. 
</P>
<P>
Broadway Deli, 1457 Third Street Promenade, Santa Monica. (213) 451-0616. 
Style: A real American bistro and foodie boutique. 
</P>
<P>
Setting: Noisy and exciting. Recommended: Caesar salad; penne with garlic; 
macaroni and cheese. Cost per person: $12-$25. 
</P>
<P>
California Pizza Kitchen, many locations including 11677 San Vicente Blvd., 
Brentwood. (213) 826-3573. Style: The People's Spago. Setting: Hospital white 
with waiting lines longer than Crystal Gayle's hair. Recommended: Vegetarian 
pizza; romaine and walnut salad; tomato and basil pasta. Cost per person: 
$10-$15. 
</P>
<P>
The Good Earth, many locations including 17212 Ventura Blvd., Encino. (818) 
986-9990. Style: Health food chain that proves food that tastes good isn't 
necessarily bad for you. Setting: 1970s -- hanging plants, wood and weavings. 
Recommended: Good Earth tostada; 10-grain pancakes; Malaysian chicken. Cost per 
person: $7-$10. 
</P>
<P>
La Salsa, many locations including 9631 Santa Monica Blvd., Beverly Hills. 
(213) 276-2373. Style: Mexican fast food chain serving good food at popular 
prices. Setting: Long counters, help-yourself salsa bar. Recommended: Burrito 
grande; carne asada, bits of grilled steak in a soft tortilla; cebollita; 
grilled scallion. Cost per person: $4-$7. 
</P>
<P>
Kentucky Fried Chicken, 340 N. Western Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 467-7421. 
Style: Cluck for a buck. Setting: This architectural delight makes you feel as 
if you are eating chicken in a chicken. Recommended: Original or Extra-Crispy, 
Kentucky nuggets. Cost per person: $2-$3. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
