<P>
Photo, Pasadena's Yesteryear: he renovation of the 84-year-old Ritz-Carlton 
Huntington Hotel in Pasadena will allow future visitors to see some of its rich 
history. Assistant Construction Supt. Steve Villegas examines an old tire ad, 
part of what may have been a car dealership in the hotel's carriage house. The 
sign won't be visible, but a joint venture between the Pasadena Historical 
Society and Gemtel Corp., which is renovating the hotel, will result in a 
1,500-square-foot museum. It will include salvaged furnishings as well as 
memorabilia from the society's collection. And the public is being asked to 
donate brochures, letters or other items that bear the hotel's name. LOU MACK / 
Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
