<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHICH IS ROACHE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have been closely following the sheriff's race, as I feel it is a very 
important race. 
</P>
<P>
Some time ago I had heard that Jim Roache, one of the candidates for sheriff, 
was opposed to the 15-day waiting period to purchase handguns. 
</P>
<P>
This concerned me greatly. 
</P>
<P>
On Aug. 29, both candidates were on a radio talk show, so I called in and asked 
specifically about this issue. Roache stated emphatically that he had never 
said he was opposed to a 15-day waiting period and he would not support 
opposition to it. 
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he said he supports the 15-day waiting period and felt it was a 
reasonable amount of time to make the required background investigations. I 
accepted what he said. 
</P>
<P>
Imagine my surprise when, only 2 1/2 weeks later, at a forum in San Diego, 
Roache stated that he was opposed to a 15-day waiting period. He felt it should 
be done more quickly. 
</P>
<P>
Now I am very confused. Does he support the 15 days or oppose it? Or is it just 
a matter of what day it is and who he is talking to? 
</P>
<P>
VIRGINIA KODADEK, San Marcos 
</P>
</TEXT>
