<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAFETY HELMETS CAN MEAN THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN LIFE, DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a mother who never considered purchasing safety helmets for my children, I 
learned the hard way just how important it is. 
</P>
<P>
After our 7-year-old son rode his bicycle into a parked vehicle this summer, he 
lost consciousness, had amnesia, a hematoma and a 4-inch crack through his 
skull. But he was one of the lucky ones -- he survived. If only we had given 
him a helmet to wear along with the responsibility that goes with riding a 
bicycle, we could have saved him, as well as our family, a lot of pain. 
</P>
<P>
Please consider a helmet to go along with that new bike this Christmas. I wish 
we had. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA FORSHEE, Yorba Linda 
</P>
</TEXT>
