<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTO SHOP WORKER INJURED IN ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An auto repair shop worker was shot and injured Saturday evening after thieves 
entered the garage on payday and robbed three employees, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified only as Fernando Briseno. 
</P>
<P>
He was listed in serious condition at UC San Diego Medical Center with a bullet 
wound in his abdomen. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego police were seeking two or three suspects. 
</P>
<P>
None of the other employees was injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbers, wearing hoods, entered the Vimoga garage in the 3700 block of Main 
Street at 7:40 p.m., police said. 
</P>
<P>
The three employees were forced to lie on the floor and were bound with toy 
handcuffs, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
The robbers took an unspecified amount of cash from the workers, police said. 
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known if the injured man had offered resistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
