<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 19; Column 3; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
82 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAYAKOA WINS SPINSTER BY 3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LEXINGTON, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bayakoa defeated arch-rival Gorgeous by three lengths to win the $268,625 Grade 
I Spinster Stakes at Keeneland Race Course on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Bayakoa covered the 1 1/8-miles over a fast track in a stakes-record 1:47 as 
Keeneland opened its fall meet. 
</P>
<P>
Jockey Laffit Pincay never whipped Bayakoa, who eased into the lead with about 
a half-mile to run. 
</P>
<P>
Bayakoa, the 4-5 favorite, paid $3.60. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was Bayakoa's sixth in nine starts and boosted her lifetime 
earnings to $2,296,273. 
</P>
</TEXT>
