<HEADLINE>
<P>
BLACK SCARS, WHITE FEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When I was a little girl and my mother would speak of conditions in South 
Africa, I would ask, "How can a handful of white people control all those black 
people?" My mother said that they didn't know the difference. 
</P>
<P>
I am about to have my first child, and I seek concrete answers for the day I am 
asked about South Africa, Germany, the Middle East and conditions in the United 
States. 
</P>
<P>
This article was very informative and honest. 
</P>
<P>
What we, as human beings, need to engrave in our lives is that life, liberty 
and the pursuit of happiness are natural inalienable rights of all people that 
no one may infringe upon. 
</P>
<P>
Scars can be healed through nurturing, and fears can be removed through 
education. From D. Ikeda: "All people are equal. There are absolutely no 
distinctions of superior and inferior among human beings." 
</P>
<P>
Keep up the outstanding work. 
</P>
<P>
JACKI SAM 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
