<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 KILLED, 1 INJURED IN CRASH ON PASADENA FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Southland residents were killed early Saturday when their car veered off 
the southbound Pasadena Freeway and struck a tree, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Driver Juvy Angel Malit, 20, of Carson was killed, along with passengers Alden 
Villacorte, 20, of Los Angeles and Cyndy Lyn Balauag, 22, of Norwalk. 
</P>
<P>
The three were pronounced dead at the scene of the accident, which occurred at 
3:15 a.m. north of the Golden State Freeway, said Officer Richard Perez of the 
California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses to the accident said the car was traveling about 70 m.p.h. in the 
fast lane, swerved into the number 3 lane and sideswiped another car, forcing 
that car to hit a three-foot-high concrete wall. The driver, Maria C. Peynado 
of Lakewood, suffered minor injuries, and three passengers in her car were 
unhurt, Perez said. 
</P>
<P>
Traffic was closed between the Golden State Freeway and Avenue 26 until 9:30 
a.m. Perez said the cause of the accident was still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
