<P>
In the Cerritos water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 11, Warren 6 -- John Lin had three goals and goalkeeper John Panagos 
had 16 saves to help Cypress (14-2) win the championship game at Cerritos 
College. 
</P>
<P>
Panagos also had 11 saves in Cypress' 12-4 victory over Kenney in a semifinal 
game. 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange County Invitational tennis tournament at Costa Mesa High School, 
Irvine freshman Milvia Schinaia defeated Holly Meyers of Marina, 6-3, 6-7, 6-1, 
to win the singles championship. In a semifinal match earlier in the day, 
Schinaia defeated her twin sister Allesandra, 6-4, 6-3. Meyers defeated Heather 
Stewart of Huntington Beach, 6-4, 6-3, to gain the final. 
</P>
