<TEXT>
<P>
In other games: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran 33, LA Baptist 14 -- Despite being outgained 231 to 147 in 
total offense, Orange Lutheran won its homecoming game. LA Baptist's hopes for 
a rally were shattered in the third quarter when the Lancers (5-0) scored 13 
points despite running only one play from scrimmage during the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Three touchdowns were scored in a 25-second margin in the quarter, two by 
Orange Lutheran without an offensive play. After Baptist's Dane Brown scored on 
an eight-yard run to cut Orange Lutheran's lead to 20-6, Phil Matheson of 
Orange Lutheran returned the kickoff 91 yards for a touchdown. Then on the next 
kickoff, the LA Baptist kick returner fumbled at the Baptist 21. Orange 
Lutheran's Lee Back one-hopped the ball and ran into the end zone, giving the 
Lancers a 33-6 lead. 
</P>
