<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOURTH-QUARTER TOUCHDOWNS LIFT DANA HILLS OVER UNIVERSITY, 24-14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
un Coleman scored two fourth-quarter touchdowns as Dana Hills High School beat 
University, 24-14, in a nonleague game Saturday night at Irvine High. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills (3-1-1) came back from a 14-0 deficit after University (2-3) had 
taken advantage of four early Dana Hills fumbles. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman scored on touchdown runs of one and five yards in the final four 
minutes. Dana Hills trailed, 14-10, with 6:30 left when the Dolphins drove 50 
yards for a touchdown. Coleman's one-yard run capped the drive and gave Dana 
Hills a 17-14 lead with 2:57 left. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Stanley of Dana Hills then recovered a fumble at the University 20 and 
three plays later, Coleman ran it in from the five to put the game out of 
reach. 
</P>
<P>
University surprised Dana Hills in the first quarter, scoring a touchdown after 
a poor snap from center on a field goal attempt. Holder Matt Selman picked up 
the low snap and hit tight end Josh Taussig for a 16-yard touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
The Trojans scored again early in the second quarter as Brian Vail threw a 
12-yard touchdown pass to Jerry Apana. University's drive, set up by Bernard 
Gardner's fumble recovery, went 60 yards in seven plays. 
</P>
<P>
But Dana Hills made it, 14-7, as quarterback Albie Sukut ran 11 yards for a 
touchdown with 7:46 left in the half. Dana Hills closed the gap to 14-10 on 
John Ashley's 35-yard field goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
