<P>
Chart, WHERE TO REGISTER ; Chart, Voter Registration Update, Los Angeles Times; 
Photo, Race for Voters Hits Homestretch: With three days left to register 
voters for the November election, county Democrats and Republicans are 
launching final recruitment drives. While the GOP, which has a clear edge, is 
recruiting countywide, the Democrats are zeroing in on the 72nd Assembly 
District, the only local area with a Democratic-voter majority. In that race, 
Democrat Tom Umberg, above, addressing supporters in Stanton, hopes to unseat 
Curt Pringle. AURELIO JOSE BARRERA / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<SUBJECT>
