<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HELD IN SIEGE OVER A $20 DEBT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN JOHNSON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Walter Phillip Hallstein wanted $20 for a wading pool he had sold to a family 
six months ago at a garage sale, say police. 
</P>
<P>
And he meant business. 
</P>
<P>
So shortly before noon Saturday, the 53-year-old Rossmoor man, toting a 
12-gauge shotgun, allegedly went to the home of David Elizondo on Yellowtail 
Drive in Rossmoor, held six adults and six children at gunpoint inside the 
house for a few minutes and collected his money, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Then he left in a white station wagon. 
</P>
<P>
After a four-hour search involving helicopters and deputies on the ground, 
Hallstein was arrested without incident with the shotgun at 3:43 p.m. at Martha 
Ann Drive and Bostonian Drive in Rossmoor, sheriff's Lt. Larry Richey said. 
</P>
<P>
Hallstein was booked into Orange County Jail on suspicion of residential 
robbery. No injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's Lt. Harold Schaffroth said, "Sometimes people do things I just can't 
believe." 
</P>
<P>
Rossmoor is an unincorporated area of about 5,000 to 6,000 homes in western 
Orange County, between Los Alamitos and Seal Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
