<LENGTH>
<P>
2288 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT / FACTS, FIGURES, COMMENTS FROM SATURDAY'S GAMES; 
</P>
<P>
NOTEWORTHY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stacey Robinson broke an NCAA quarterback rushing record with 308 yards, and 
scored five touchdowns, in Northern Illinois' 73-18 rout of No. 24 Fresno 
State. Robinson broke the record of 294 set by Nolan Cromwell of Kansas against 
Oregon State in 1975. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Gardocki kicked a school record-tying four field goals, from 47, 25, 30 
and 25 yards, in Clemson's 34-3 victory over Georgia. It was the largest margin 
of victory by Clemson over Georgia since 1905, when the Tigers won, 35-0. 
Clemson's Doug Brewster set up a field goal in the second quarter when he 
blocked Scot Armstrong's punt, the first block against the Bulldogs since 1984. 
</P>
<P>
John Langeloh kicked an extra point in Michigan State's 12-7 loss to Iowa, 
tying him with Morten Andersen as the Spartans' career scoring leader with 261 
points. Langeloh missed field-goal attempts of 19 and 42 yards. 
</P>
<P>
David Klingler, the nation's total offense leader, completed 35 of 68 passes 
for 405 yards in Houston's 31-15 Southwest Conference victory over Baylor. 
Klingler was one short of Andre Ware's school and conference record for pass 
attempts. 
</P>
<P>
Mississippi defeated Kentucky, 35-29, for its third consecutive victory and 
improved its record to 4-1, the best start for the Rebels since quarterback 
Archie Manning led the 1970 team to a 4-1 record after five games. The victory 
was Billy Brewer's 100th as a college coach. 
</P>
<P>
The Colorado State defense made the difference in a 22-13 victory over Utah. 
The Rams sacked Utah quarterback Jason Woods seven times, intercepted three of 
his passes and recovered two fumbles. 
</P>
<P>
Illinois' 31-20 victory over Ohio State was its third in a row, the first time 
the Illini have beaten the Buckeyes three games in a row since 1927-29. 
</P>
<P>
Phillip Doyle's six field goals tied a Southeastern Conference record in 
Alabama's 25-6 victory over Southwestern Louisiana. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Musgrave became Oregon's all-time offense leader in the No. 22 Ducks' 52-7 
victory over Utah State. Musgrave completed 15 of 23 passes for 187 yards and 
increased his career offense total to 6,878 yards. He surpassed the previous 
school record of 6,841 set from 1983-86 by quarterback Chris Miller. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
STREAKS 
</P>
<P>
Penn State's 48-10 victory over Temple was the Nittany Lions' 16th consecutive 
win over its intrastate rival since the teams played a tie in 1950. 
</P>
<P>
Colgate's Dave Goodwin, who passed for three touchdowns in a 30-7 victory over 
Yale, has thrown touchdown passes in nine consecutive games, breaking the 
school record of Steve Calabria set in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
Michigan's 41-3 victory over Wisconsin was the Wolverines' ninth in a row over 
the Badgers since 1981. 
</P>
