<P>
GIVE 'EM FIVE 
</P>
<P>
From the "If at first you don't succeed, try, try, try, try, try again 
department: Colorado, ranked No. 12, avoided an upset by Missouri, 33-31, 
scoring on the last play of the game. And on fifth down. 
</P>
<P>
The final sequence, according to the official play by play, was an incomplete 
pass on first down, a short run on second, no gain on a run on third and 
another incomplete pass on fourth. Fourth down, Part II: Charles Johnson runs 
into the end zone. Seems everyone forgot about the first incomplete pass. By 
the time everyone realized that Missouri had been Buffaloed, it was too late. 
Officials said they could not reverse the decision once the play had taken 
place. 
</P>
<P>
WHAT I MEANT WAS... 
</P>
<P>
Terrell Buckley, a sophomore cornerback for previously undefeated Florida 
State, dismissed the talents of Miami quarterback Craig Erickson when 
interviewed before the CBS telecast of Miami's 31-22 victory. Buckley said he 
hadn't seen anything in Erickson's performance that would qualify him as a 
Heisman Trophy candidate and said he considered the Miami quarterback only an 
"average" player. Good thing for Buckley Erickson's an only average 
quarterback. Erickson passed to Buckley's side with effectiveness, including a 
10-yard scorig pass to Lamar Thomas in the second quarter on which Buckley was 
beaten by at least a couple of steps. 
</P>
<P>
INJURIES 
</P>
<P>
Army running back Willie McMillian left the game against Duke in the fourth 
quarter with a pulled right hamstring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
