<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moorpark 20, L.A. Southwest 7 -- Freddie Bradley rushed for 154 yards on 22 
carries and scored all three Moorpark touchdowns in a Western State Conference 
game at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
Bradley scored on runs of one, six and 58 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark (4-0, 3-0) ran the ball on 45 of its 62 offensive plays. 
</P>
<P>
Southwest (1-3, 0-3) quarterback Craig Manigo, who completed 14 of 31 passes 
for 189 yards, hit Robert Avery with a 30-yard touchdown pass to cut Moorpark's 
lead to 14-7 in the fourth quarter. But Bradley scored his final touchdown to 
secure the victory. 
</P>
<P>
"I think Bradley sets them apart from everyone else," Southwest Coach Henry 
Washington said. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark has a showdown next week against Bakersfield, which is also 
undefeated. 
</P>
