<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bakersfield 62, Ventura 20 -- Sophomore Shon Ellerbe rushed for 209 yards and 
four touchdowns to lead Bakersfield (4-0, 3-0) in a WSC game at Larrabee 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura (0-4, 0-2) rushed for only 36 yards in 20 first-half carries. The 
Renegades totaled 333 yards in 37 carries en route to a 41-6 halftime bulge. 
</P>
<P>
But Ventura played inspired defense in the first quarter and trailed 
Bakersfield, 7-6, after quarterback Tim Albrent tossed a 10-yard touchdown pass 
to wide receiver Chris Thomas on the second play of the second quarter. PAUL 
OLSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
