<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SAME MAN MAY HAVE ATTACKED 3 WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THIA BELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The man who raped an Ojai woman Thursday morning could be responsible for two 
other assaults in the Ojai area this year, officials said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
"We think it might be the same person. 
</P>
<P>
If we get him identified, it could tie them all together. But until we do, we 
can't say for sure," said Sgt. Tom Odle of the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Victims of the three attacks have given similar descriptions of their 
assailant, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect is described as in his mid-20s, slender, about 5 feet 6 inches tall 
with light brown skin, dark brown hair and brown or hazel eyes. 
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, a 25-year-old Ojai woman reported that she was raped about 1:30 
a.m. after she was dragged into a downtown mini-mall at the corner of Aliso and 
North Signal streets. 
</P>
<P>
The woman told police that she made a call from a public phone on Matilija 
Street and was walking back to her apartment when she was accosted, Odle said. 
When the man let her go, he drove away in a yellow car, Odle said. 
</P>
<P>
On March 16, a 20-year-old Meiners Oaks woman was jogging through a field on 
Maricopa Highway north of Nordhoff High School in mid-afternoon when a man 
grabbed her. 
</P>
<P>
Passersby heard her screams and ran to help her. The man rode off on a yellow 
mountain bike and eluded deputies. 
</P>
<P>
On June 24, deputies who answered a resident's call of hearing screams about 9 
p.m. encountered a woman struggling with a man on the ground in Nordhoff 
Cemetery at Cuyama and Del Norte roads. The man fled. 
</P>
<P>
That 25-year-old woman told police that her car broke down and that she was 
looking for a phone when the man dragged her into the cemetery. THIA BELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
